      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "df3f6dd6e57a9ddd",
        "text": "# Design process of a game\n\n1) I start with a set of principles I read and experimented in existing organizations\n\n2) I define the scope of the game for it not to last more than 2 hours in average: its goal and what it will concretely produce\n\n3) I write down the phases/big steps of the games: they become the rounds of the game\n\n4) I define the roles for the players and the relationship between the roles: they become the role cards\n\n5) I define the set of tools (opensource apps) to be used by eahc role and the actions to be completed by each role: they become the action cards\n\n6) I go back and forth between steps 3),4) and 5) to make it consistent: I define an accurate timing for each action cards to be completed\n\n7) During step 6), generally I think of already existing games I played before and remix the gme mecanics of 1 (or sometimes several of them). I pay a special attention to Roger Caillois 4 moods of the games: aleas, ilynx, mimicry and agon.\n\n8) I write down the rules\n9) I produce all the cards, the board with paper, pens, and basic collage\n10) I produce the designs of the collage for the cards and the board\n\n11) I test the timing of the game with players\n\n12) I go do some hard design with artists: for example lasercutter of leather for the board, or serigraphic on textile, or simple on cardboard. (not completed yet)\n13) I publish the game online: text + svg and pdf files. Of 3d printing needed: stl files (didn't try 3d printed pawns yet)\n14) Small production and Animation process."
      },
      "date": 1524062905312
    },
